{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fully fund specialist glasses for visually impaired children",
        "additional_details": "We call on the Government to require the NHS to fully fund specialist glasses, tinted lenses, and visual aids for visually impaired children, including those without a standard prescription.\r\nCurrent NHS vouchers often fail to cover the true cost, forcing families to pay for essential medical aids. This creates a postcode lottery where children\u2019s access to vital visual support depends on where they live and what their family can afford.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to fully fund clinically necessary specialist glasses and tinted lenses for all visually impaired children through the NHS.",
